%HRTitleEvent Reverse
[Event "Baker Bridge - Reverse Bids"]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "1"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "N:AK.52.A642.AKT74 QJ853.AT76.QT.32 T74.KJ98.K73.985 962.Q43.J985.QJ6"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "3C"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
1C pass 1H pass 2D pass 3C pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 1, chOption: N, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 0, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_bids"]
[Student "S"]
{You would really love to pass. You have a terrible hand and you like the \Ds better than the \Cs.

But you are forced to bid. And since partner has 5 \Cs and only 4 \Ds, you should take him back to his first suit.

Mercifully he passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "W:J7.AK63.KQT85.KT A98432.J2.3.8642 KQT5.Q8.J94.QJ97 6.T9754.A762.A53"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
1D pass 1S pass 2H pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_bids"]
[Student "S"]
{When partner shows 17+ points with his Reverse you are sure you belong in game. Since he did not support your \Ss you know he doesn't have four of them. You also know you have an 8-card fit in \Ds, but surely nine tricks in Notrump will be easier than eleven in \Ds.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "S:63.K5.KQJ6.AKT72 JT87.QJ97.AT2.Q6 Q52.A863.753.843 AK94.T42.984.J95"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "3C"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1C pass 1H pass 2D pass 3C pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 2, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_bids"]
[Student "S"]
{With 17 points you have a perfect hand for a Reverse. So you bid 2\D. Partner then says 3\C.  

Partner's return to your \C suit shows he has fewer than 9 points. Although it is possible to devise a hand for him where your side could make 3NT, the risk is too great.

So you pass. It's a good thing, too.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:J73.J.AK64.AK983 AK962.A6.T975.42 T85.KQ9874.83.76 Q4.T532.QJ2.QJT5"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "2H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1C pass 1H pass 2D pass 2H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_bids"]
[Student "S"]
{You have 7 points, and basically nothing but s\H. You must make a minimum bid, and the only reasonable one is 2\H. Despite his 17 points, partner passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "N:7.AQJ9.KQJ764.A3 Q9542.T8.A53.KT2 AK86.72.T98.7654 JT3.K6543.2.QJ98"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "5D"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
1D pass 1S pass 2H pass 3D pass 5D pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: N, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 2, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_bids"]
[Student "S"]
{You have an ideal hand for a Reverse, so you bid 2\H.

Partner now bids 3\D.  

Partner has a minimum hand, but at least he came up with a preference for \Ds.

There are no guarantees here, but you should probably try 5\D.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "6"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "W:J5.AT.AQJ3.KQ986 AT8.KQ93.9642.54 KQ9743.872.K5.T3 62.J654.T87.AJ72"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
1C pass 1S pass 2D pass 3S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 6, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_bids"]
[Student "S"]
{With 18 points you have enough to make a Reverse. So you bid 2\D. Partner now says 3\S.  

Partner's jump bid shows a 6-card suit and enough points to insist on game. With your \H stopper you might be considering 3NT, but since you know of an 8-card \S fit you decide on 4\S.

Be very glad that you did.3NT would go down with a \H opening lead while 4\S is cold.}

